I am going to work on Yellow Card, Ocean Avenue in memory and to keep the memory of my best Army and Theatre friend, Sargent Brady J Sikorski. It was the only song he couldn't master for his summer entertainment job at Cedar Point in Sandusky Ohio. Oh, I failed to mention we were both born in Ohio-- me at least 5? Years older than Brady. We met when I moved to Atlanta Georgia, my bf dumped me and so I moved closer to work in midtown. Brady and i connected during a group run with Front Runners, Atlanta. While we never dated, he was like a younger version of my older brother who also served in the military. Kind, generous, happy, inclusive, etc. For his kindness, respect and encouragement I will always be grateful. My life has been empty since you returned to Heaven. I only hope that my love and total submission to Gött will reunite us in the far future. See, when Brady died so did an Angel that walked amoung us on this here blue marble we call Earth. The only known or even predicted habitable planet in the Universe. The more we scientist learn, the more our Gött revealsv or shows of his design. Calculations beyond chance at 10^18 power of accuracy for many factors (distance to the sun, placement of Jupiter to protect the Earth from meteor strikes, thickness of the crust/mantle, amount of nitrogen, oxygen, hydrogen and helium in our breathable atmosphere, the amount of drinkable water, gardens and animals provided for nutrients, corn for food, ethanol fuel, animal feed, even base material for takeaway containers and utensils --to name a few. Humans are the only species that inquisitive to want to know why and how something arbeiten.", "Wow. I forgot about this song and how much it reminds me of my life. No choice but to find a place two days after High School graduation. Government support ends at the age of 18 or once graduated from high school, whichever comes first. Unfortunately, our apartment lease aligned with the school year. Nothing like packing while trying to study and finish school for Uni.

Fortunately a friend and his parents adopted me when i met him in 1984, we graduated in 1991. Unfortunately we were as far apart in the city as we could be for two people that had parents or a non driving parent. We were probably 30 miles apart, but it was 3 hours by bus and required 5 miles of walking to see each other at least once a month. Anyway, thanks Ed. You saved my life numerous times the year offer the past ten months. Feel free to go over and hear me attempt to reproduce a fraction of your gift.

I had my access to the outside world removed for 35 days 10/03/23-11/07/23. you and i ❤', 'i love little freak this is my favourite song i love you HARRY STYLES joi so italy', 'Happy Halloween.', 'This song is so special to me because I started listening to Harry’s music just because of it and now I can‘t imagine not to.
Me and my best friend played Drag me Down when we were younger and when it first came out, then the first solo song, we would always watch the Sign of the times music video and sing along to it. Then I never really listend to Harry’s music anymore because we both found new artists that we loved at that time.
July 2022 I was on a summer holiday trip with that same best friend and we were in the car and the radio was on.
A song played and my dad asked wich song that was and my best friend said ,, that’s As it was by Harry Styles“.
I‘ve heard it before on the internet but I never really payed much attention to it and that evening after hearing As it was on the radio I scrolled through YouTube and a lot of videos of Harry’s concerts were on my page. People screaming ,, Leave America“ and other fun stuff.
Every day I watched more videos like those and started to like it a lot, but I didn‘t listened to the new album at that time.
A few weeks after the summer trip I saw a clip and Little freak was playing in the background but not the full song.
So then I finally listend to the whole song and it was immediately my new favorite song. I played it every day when I went to bed and it became such a special song to me.
I started listening to the full album and to the other albums more and more, my taste on every song has changed a cupple of times but Little Freak always stayed my favorite.
Since then I‘ve watched Don‘t Worry Darling with my best friend in the theater, watched My Policeman, the Grammys, the Brits and then I went to two amazing concerts in Munich and Frankfurt and now I can‘t wait to experience that again.
I‘m really glad I found my way into this absolutely amazing fandom and I‘m so excited for anything that’s coming next.\U0001faf6🏻

['This is my most favorite Song!', 'This is one of my favourite songs from her and has probably the most important message in the album. The speaker is reminiscing back on their life and feel that it is abruptly coming to an end. That is why they are thinking about the things they really want to do in their last moments, for someone to just hear them out and understand them, tell them lies like things are going to be alright, to make them believe that love is real and life is all worth it. The speaker is obviously despairing. They want it all to matter towards the end. They want someone to just notice them and to feel how they are feeling at such a despondent state.
"Sorry, can't save me now. Sorry I don't know how. Sorry there's no way out, but down."
By the end, they are saying their goodbyes. They are sorry for their actions and for carrying on with the deed. They know that there is no saving them, or that they can turn back. They are fixed towards the idea. They need to k*ll themselves.

I listen to this when my heart has stopped feeling everything. It's when I can't bring myself to cry even more. And it's always felt more of a comfort really instead of being sad. It makes me feel like I'm not alone in feeling this way, that some other lost soul out there knows and has gone through what I am going through. And instead on ruminating over all that darkness, Billie has been generous enough to turn those feelings into a heartfelt song. She is my saviour in a way, and I am grateful for having written her demons down into paper.

['Perfectionistic Thinking and Behavior

Many people think of perfectionism as something positive as it is mistakenly seen as a pursuit of excellence. People hold the belief that aiming for perfection allows them to be efficient, organized, and prepared. However, perfectionism can have the opposite effect. Perfectionism is a paradox. As one’s perfectionism increases, they are most likely to feel frustrated and upset rather than fulfilled. \xa0Setting high expectations can be motivating and quite healthy. However, when taken to the extreme, our productivity can actually decrease. Perfectionists frequently experience many of the symptoms listed below:

Fear of failure.\xa0Perfectionists often equate failure to achieve their goals with a lack of personal worth or value.

Fear of making mistakes.\xa0Perfectionists often equate mistakes with failure. In orienting their lives around avoiding mistakes, perfectionists miss opportunities to learn and grow.

Fear of disapproval.\xa0If they let others see their flaws, perfectionists often fear that they will no longer be accepted. Trying to be perfect is a way of trying to protect themselves from criticism, rejection, and disapproval.

All-or-none thinking.\xa0Perfectionists frequently believe that they are worthless if their accomplishments are not perfect. Perfectionists have difficulty seeing situations in perspective. For example, a “straight A” student who receives a “B” might believe, “I am a total failure.”

Overcompensating.\xa0Performing a behavior in an excessive manner to try to ensure nothing goes wrong

Excessive Checking and Reassurance Seeking.\xa0Checking and/or seeking reassurance from others that a task has been done well enough or that all standards are met

Excessive Organizing and List Making.\xa0Spending so much time getting organized that it interfere with getting tasks completed

Procrastination:\xa0Putting off doing things for fear of not meeting standards

Avoidance.\xa0Avoiding doing something altogether for fear of not meeting standards.', "Madonna is the Queen of Pop, there was Nobody like Madonna before there was Madonna.

['Oh m gosh, like, you won't believe how cray-cray my journey with T-Swift's music has been, like, seriously. So, like, at first, I was, like, totally not into her tunes, you know? I mean, everyone was all like, "T-Swift is, like, the queen of pop," and I was just rolling my eyes, thinking, "Ugh, basic much?" But then, one day, I accidentally hit play on one of her songs, and, like, my whole world just, like, flipped.

I, like, couldn't stop listening to her music; it was like she was singing the story of my life, you know? Each song was, like, a chapter of my own drama-filled novel. And, oh my gosh, when I went to my first T-Swift concert, it was, like, totally life-changing. The vibes, the energy, the drama—everything was so on point. I felt like T-Swift was, like, singing just for me, even though there were, like, thousands of people there.

Now, like, I'm totally obsessed with T-Swift, and I don't even care if it's, like, basic or whatever. Her music is, like, the soundtrack of my life, and her concerts are, like, my happy place. I'm, like, living my best life, all thanks to T-Swift. Like, seriously, can we just, like, shake it off and, like, dance like nobody's watching? ['Heyyy, I know you're probably busy so I'll keep this short, so it's my friend's birthday on 23 November and I just want you to reply "Happy Birthday Chhavi" if at all possible, please, please, please, she's one of your biggest fans for real and I'm sure she'd love to see that her favourite artist wished her for her birthday, so yeah, please ❤️🙏🏻 (Gonna try to post this on every video of yours in hope you see and reply<333))', 'The chorus of this song is what I imagine the gates of Heaven sounding like', "I had a little mental breakdown while playing songs on Spotify so i stopped the music for i little while. I cried. I was thinking about how i'm considered beautiful from everybody (friends, family strangers) but nobody bothers to love, to try to have me, no one really approaches me. So i was crying, thinking why am i so alone and so lonely and desired but at the same time not wanted. I decided to stop crying because i know that saddness stays on people's faces with age and i want to look positive and happy, a have wrinkles from laughter ( just me overthinking the sh!t out of everything). So i reached to play the next songs and guess what started playing. And it was the first time i hear this song (i'm a new taylor swift fan). When i heard the chorus i just looked at the screen and started crying all over again. It was ugly crying but i've never felt more beautiful. And she WAS talking to me in that moment. It was so real. That meant everything for me in that moment.
So thank whatever force was responsible for that.
For everybody that does not feel the love they need. I'm with you, and we will be okay. It WILL happen and it's meant for us. Understand that you are as perfect as you can be and somebody will fully appreciate that some day. You and I, we will get there! Got it? Got it!
❤️", 'How can I make this sort of thing??', 'THIS SONG IS SO UNDERRATED AND ITS ONE OF MY FAVORITES', 'Taylor is my favorite singer', 'I love this song', 'This is definitely one of my top three Taylor's songs. The angellical  voice, how poetical the lyrics are, the majestuous golden aesthetic..
But most of all, it's because this song reminds me of someone that I don't even know if I loved, or at least I liked. We were never on something romantic, because we're partners and all of that stuff. But when I was still analyzing what did I felt for this person, "a friend" of mine that was upset with me told them about the fact that I was in love with them, and this person is lowkey more distant with me now. I must confess that I said to this friend of mine that I had a crush on this person, but they weren't suposed to tell them..
This song reminds me of that crush because how the lyrics say that "I don't love someone that everybody wants to date", and seems to be a perfect person. But all of these fantasies just vanish in a certain moment.
